.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH g-add 1  "g-add " 
.SH NAME
g\-add \- Stage files interactively, or forward arguments to `git add`
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBg\-add\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIARGS\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Stage files interactively, or forward arguments to `git add`
.PP
With no arguments an interactive multi\-select picker is shown so you can choose exactly which files to stage using ↑↓ / j k and Space. Any flags or paths you supply are forwarded to `git add` unchanged.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
[\fIARGS\fR]
Extra arguments forwarded to git
